The in-scope features define the functionalities that are included in CookSnap â€“ 
Smart Recipe Recommendation System Using Grocery Images. These features are essential for enabling users to identify available groceries and receive suitable 
recipe recommendations efficiently.

In-Scope Features

Grocery Image Upload:
Users can upload images of available groceries using the system.

Ingredient Detection:
The system automatically identifies grocery items from the uploaded images using image recognition techniques.

Recipe Recommendation:
Based on the detected ingredients, the system suggests relevant and suitable recipes.

Recipe Details Display:
Users can view detailed recipe information including ingredients and preparation steps.

Filtering Options:
Users can filter recipes based on preferences such as vegetarian or non-vegetarian options.

User Authentication:
Secure login and access control for registered users.

User-Friendly Interface:
A simple and intuitive interface for easy interaction with the system.

Basic Usage Statistics:
The system provides basic statistics such as number of recipes viewed or recommended.
